'''''Star Wars Tech''''' is a [[Wikipedia:Documentary Film|documentary]] about the technical aspects of ''[[Star Wars]]'', from [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] robotic limbs to the [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] to how an [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] compares to modern jets. The one-hour program (46 minutes without commercials) debuted on [[Wikipedia:The History Channel|The History Channel]] on [[May 28]], [[2007]], coinciding roughly with the 30-year anniversary of ''Star Wars''. The program was later released on [[Star Wars home video releases|DVD]] and was included in the [[Star Wars: The Complete Saga|''Star Wars'' saga Blu-Ray box set]].<ref name="TFNSWBD">{{WebCite|url=http://theforce.net/latestnews/story/MTFBWY_SW_BluRay_Details_Released_137998.asp|text=MTFBWY: SW Blu-Ray Details Released|author=Geller, Eric|date=2011-05-04|work=[[TheForce.net]]|archivedate=20190730154757}}</ref>

